sponseType":"sba","marks":1,"options":["Insulin injections","Oral insulin","GLP-1 agonists","Metformin","Sulfonylureas"],"correctOptions":[0],"correctResponses":null,"explanation":"\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EInsulin injections\u003C/strong\u003E are the cornerstone of type 1 diabetes management. Patients with type 1 diabetes have an absolute deficiency of insulin due to autoimmune destruction of pancreatic beta cells, necessitating lifelong insulin therapy to maintain blood glucose control.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EOral insulin\u003C/strong\u003E is not a suitable option as it is made of peptides and the acidic environment of the stomach would break it down, rendering it ineffective. Insulin must be administered via injection or an insulin pump.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EGLP-1 agonists\u003C/strong\u003E are used in the management of type 2 diabetes to enhance insulin secretion and reduce appetite. They are not used in type 1 diabetes management as they do not address the underlying insulin deficiency.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EMetformin\u003C/strong\u003E is an oral medication used in type 2 diabetes to improve insulin sensitivity. It is not a standard treatment for type 1 diabetes, although it may be used in some cases of insulin resistance.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003ESulfonylureas\u003C/strong\u003E stimulate insulin secretion from the pancreas and are used in type 2 diabetes. They are ineffective in type 1 diabetes due to the lack of functional beta cells.\u003C/p\u003E","optionExplanations":["","","","",""],"learningPoints":["Type 1 diabetes management requires lifelong insulin therapy.","Oral insulin is not available; insulin must be administered via injection or pump.","GLP-1 agonists are not used in type 1 diabetes management."],"references":["Holt RIG, DeVries JH, Hess-Fischl A, Hirsch IB, Kirkman MS, Klupa T, Ludwig B, N\u00f8rgaard K, Pettus J, Renard E, Skyler JS, Snoek FJ, Weinstock RS, Peters AL. The management of type 1 diabetes in adults. A consensus report by the American Diabetes Association (ADA) and the European Association for the Study of Diabetes (EASD). Diabetologia. 2021 Dec;64(12):2609-2652. doi: 10.1007/s00125-021-05568-3. Erratum in: Diabetologia. 2022 Jan;65(1):255. doi: 10.1007/s00125-021-05600-6. PMID: 34590174; PMCID: PMC8481000.","Aschner P, Horton E, Leiter LA, Munro N, Skyler JS; Global Partnership for Effective Diabetes Management. Practical steps to improving the management of type 1 diabetes: recommendations from the Global Partnership for Effective Diabetes Management. Int J Clin Pract. 2010 Feb;64(3):305-15. doi: 10.1111/j.1742-1241.2009.02296.x. PMID: 20456170; PMCID: PMC2814087.","Smith A, Harris C. Type 1 Diabetes: Management Strategies. Am Fam Physician. 2018 Aug 1;98(3):154-162. PMID: 30215903."]},"relationships":{"itemRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"61334"}},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"17926"}},"stemMedia":{"data":[]},"explanationMedia":{"data":[]}}},{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"61334","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/itemRevisions/61334"},"attributes":{"createdAt":"2024-12-31T17:04:20+10:30","updatedAt":"2024-12-31T17:04:20+10:30"},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"10640"}},"content":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"75821"}}},"meta":{"canDelete":false}},{"type":"tags","id":"4","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/4"},"attributes":{"emoji":"\ud83c\udf6c","name":"Endocrinology","synonyms":[],"description":null,"position":null,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":"2024-11-21T09:49:43+10:30"},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"1"}},"heading":{"data":{"type":"tagHeadings","id":"1"}}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"type":"tags","id":"9","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/9"},"attributes":{"emoji":"\ud83d\udc76","name":"Paediatrics","synonyms":[],"description":null,"position":null,"createdAt":null,"up